8 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to ivermectin; defining term;
allowing ivermectin to be sold or purchased without
10 prescription; providing for immunity; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 355.5 of Title 59, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. As used in this section, "over-the-counter medication" means
19 medication that may be legally sold and purchased without
20 prescription.
21 B. Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, ivermectin suitable
22 for human use may be sold or purchased as an over-the-counter
23 medication in this state without a prescription or consultation with
24 a health care professional.
Req. No. 16077 Page 1

1 C. Notwithstanding any other law, a pharmacy is not criminally
2 or civilly liable for supplying ivermectin in accordance with this
3 section.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
